The Gaol At Dongri, Bombay &ldquo;You are sentenced to fifty years&rsquo; transportation. The International Tribunal at Hague has given judgement that England cannot be constrained to hand you over to France&rdquo;, said Mr. X to me.
&ldquo;Well then, I had never depended on any hopes from that quarter. But can I have a copy of the judgement to look at?&rdquo;
&ldquo;That does not rest with me, though I will try my very best for you.
